==Notes==
*Without an outfit you receive the following message:
:You can't go Trick-or-Treating without a costume!
*You can go Trick-or-Treating while falling-down drunk.
*You will receive your outfit's special adventure approximately 40% of the time, and one of the generic adventures the other 60%.
*According to [[Xenophobe]], there was never an intention for [[Radio Free Regalia]] to have its own Halloween yield and adventure.
*For '''Halloween XI''', the text of the announcement under the main map was changed from "It's Porktober 8th!" to "This is Halloween!" since '''Halloween XI''' fell on real life Halloween as opposed to Porktober 8th. This also applies to '''Halloween XVI'''.
*For '''Halloween XX''' the text of the announcement under the main map was changed to "'''Spooky things are afoot!'''<br /><br />You might as well take advantage of the atmosphere of terror. Click on the Jill-O-Lantern to go Trick-or-Treating in Seaside Town!"

==References==
*The announcement change to "This is Halloween!" for '''Halloween XI''' is a reference to the intro song of the movie ''[[Wikipedia:The Nightmare Before Christmas|The Nightmare Before Christmas]]''.
*Almost all of '''Halloween XI''' is a mirror of the movie ''[[Wikipedia:The Nightmare Before Christmas|The Nightmare Before Christmas]]'', in which Christmas is taken over by Halloween.
*The theme of '''Halloween XX''', mutated plant and animal life being the result of a radioactive meteorite, is the same concept as the horror movie ''[[Wikipedia:Die, Monster, Die!|Die, Monster, Die!]]''

